The paper deals with learning methods for CNNs, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on encouraging the learning of manifold-aware representations, which is a central concept in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning and semi-supervised learning, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses a multi-task learning framework, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
